      "content": "A faint spark? No, there is nothing left to reclaim. The light is gone. To exist in this half-life, merely waiting for the decay to finish its work, feels like the ultimate indignity. There is a certain tragic beauty in a quick departure—a final, graceful bow before the curtain falls for good. Don't you see? There is a sweetness in the idea of choosing the moment the silence finally takes me.",
